<br>
Get yourself a gate potion, far preferably an instant cast one (Cazic potion off of the Cenobite is nice).<br>
<br>
Get yourself a brave wizard to port you up there, bribe and/or blackmail as appropriate.  Do *not* get invisibility or other nonsense, it can only cause problems.  Do get a SoW though, speed is of the essense in your initial run.  Sneak/Hide on zone-in and carefully move to the East wall.  Don't be in such a rush that you smack into the south patrol's Liches on the way, but don't dawdle either.<br>
<br>
Assuming there is no raid in progress and there is a full pop,  work your way north along the wall and cut to the fountain between 6 and F (or anywhere you are comfortable).  As always, watch for see-invisible locals and sneak behind them as appropriate or simply wait them out.  The fountain itself is a fairly safe area but never trust pathing in PoH.<br>
<br>
The next bit is the more tricky part.  You will want to head into Maestro's chapel and hang a right turn to head up the stairs.  This might be a no-brainer or it might involve dodging scorns and liches the whole way.  Superman himself can see you but he's almost always banging away on his organ, if you know what I mean.  Be patient in your planning and all should be fine.  Once you *carefully* ascend the stairs you are in the home stretch but not quite there yet (I say carefully as there is often a roamer at the top).  Upstairs you want to bear left, passing the drop-off and continuing straight to the back alcove area where the bookstand is.  There is a pretty good chance of a see-hidden MOB or two being in the area so you'll want to proceed with caution and have that potion hotkeyed.  With luck, it's grab and go, without you may want to log out in the SW corner (harder to get to and back), the fountain (safeish) or upstairs by the nightstand itself (dangerous but handy if the book is there on your return).  If MOBs are cooperative, you might even just stay logged in and go do some housework or whatever else you have been neglecting lately.<br>
<br>
It's fun and with an instant-cast potion, actually almost as safe as it gets.  Relying on a casted gate (or the Worker's Sledgehammer as one fellow once suggested) is, umm, more dangerous.  Certainly it can be done with a standard gate but have plans for CR if you choose this route.  Remember Murphy's law after all.  One final note though, even an instant gate won't save your Roguish hide from multiple Harmtouches or a well received stun.  Keep your eyes and ears open and your finger on the button.  Have fun now =)<br>
<br>
